{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879053393,"sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa3dbb0001HeqdUAhMKLF3eX","messageID":"msg_d7aa3c639001nETap8AVBJkyib","sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b0495604dcf74432910b4cd6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Chart Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: manifests/charts/base/\n13: ├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n14: ├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n15: ├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n16: ├── crds/\n17: │   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n18: │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n19: └── templates/\n20:     ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions\n21:     ├── redis-secret.yaml               # Redis password Secret\n22:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml            # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n23:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml           # Router Deployment + Service\n24:     ├── rbac/\n25:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml        # WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n26:     ├── rbac-router.yaml                # Optional Router RBAC\n27:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ### Component Diagram\n31: \n32: ```\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                    Helm Chart (agentcube)                        │\n35: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n36:                               │\n37:                               │ helm install/upgrade\n38:                               ▼\n39: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                   Kubernetes Cluster                             │\n41: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐ │\n42: │  │     Router       │  │ WorkloadManager  │  │   Volcano     │ │\n43: │  │  Deployment      │  │   Deployment     │  │   Scheduler   │ │\n44: │  │  + Service       │  │   + Service      │  │  (optional)   │ │\n45: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └───────────────┘ │\n46: │           │                      │                               │\n47: │           └──────────┬───────────┘                               │\n48: │                      │                                           │\n49: │           ┌──────────▼───────────┐                               │\n50: │           │   Redis Secret        │                               │\n51: │           │   (password store)    │                               │\n52: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n53: │                                                                   │\n54: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n55: │           │   RBAC Resources      │                               │\n56: │           │   (SA, Role, Binding) │                               │\n57: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n58: │                                                                   │\n59: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n60: │           │      CRDs             │                               │\n61: │           │  agentruntimes,       │                               │\n62: │           │  codeinterpreters     │                               │\n63: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n64: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### Integration Points\n68: \n69: - **Redis**: External dependency for session storage (address/password from values)\n70: - **Volcano Scheduler**: Optional component for advanced scheduling\n71: - **RBAC**: WorkloadManager requires cluster-wide permissions; Router RBAC is optional\n72: - **CRDs**: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n73: \n74: ## Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### Chart.yaml Metadata\n77: \n78: ```yaml\n79: apiVersion: v1\n80: name: agentcube\n81: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n82: version: 0.1.0\n83: appVersion: \"1.0.0\"\n84: keywords:\n85:   - agent\n86:   - sandbox\n87:   - kubernetes\n88:   - volcano\n89: maintainers:\n90:   - name: Volcano Authors\n91:     email: volcano-sh@googlegroups.com\n92: home: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n93: sources:\n94:   - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### values.yaml Configuration Tree\n98: \n99: ```yaml\n100: # Global settings\n101: imagePullSecrets: []\n102: nameOverride: \"\"\n103: fullnameOverride: \"\"\n104: \n105: # Redis configuration (required)\n106: redis:\n107:   addr: \"\"           # Required: Redis address (e.g., \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\")\n108:   password: \"\"       # Optional: Redis password for authentication\n109: \n110: # Router component\n111: router:\n112:   replicas: 1\n113:   image:\n114:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n115:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n116:     tag: \"latest\"\n117:   service:\n118:     type: ClusterIP\n119:     port: 8080\n120:     targetPort: 8080\n121:   resources:\n122:     limits:\n123:       cpu: 500m\n124:       memory: 512Mi\n125:     requests:\n126:       cpu: 100m\n127:       memory: 128Mi\n128:   config: {}                      # Additional container configuration\n129:   extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n130:   serviceAccountName: \"\"          # Empty for default/auto-generated\n131:   rbac:\n132:     create: false                 # Disable RBAC by default\n133: \n134: # WorkloadManager component\n135: workloadmanager:\n136:   replicas: 1\n137:   image:\n138:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n139:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n140:     tag: \"latest\"\n141:   service:\n142:     type: ClusterIP\n143:     port: 8080\n144:   resources:\n145:     limits:\n146:       cpu: 500m\n147:       memory: 512Mi\n148:     requests:\n149:       cpu: 100m\n150:       memory: 128Mi\n151:   extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n152: \n153: # Volcano Scheduler (optional)\n154: volcano:\n155:   scheduler:\n156:     enabled: false                # Disabled by default\n157:     replicas: 1\n158:     image:\n159:       repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n160:       pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n161:       tag: \"latest\"\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### Environment Variables\n165: \n166: | Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n167: |----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n168: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | `fieldRef: metadata.namespace` |\n169: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis connection address | `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}` |\n170: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis authentication | `Secret {{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password` |\n171: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | Constructed: `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}` |\n172: \n173: ## API Contracts\n174: \n175: ### Template Contracts\n176: \n177: #### WorkloadManager Deployment\n178: \n179: ```yaml\n180: apiVersion: apps/v1\n181: kind: Deployment\n182: metadata:\n183:   name: workloadmanager\n184:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n185:   labels:\n186:     app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager\n187:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n188: spec:\n189:   replicas: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}\n190:   selector:\n191:     matchLabels:\n192:       app: workloadmanager\n193:   template:\n194:     metadata:\n195:       labels:\n196:         app: workloadmanager\n197:     spec:\n198:       serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\n199:       containers:\n200:       - name: workloadmanager\n201:         image: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\n202:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}\n203:         args:\n204:         - --port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n205:         - --runtime-class-name=\n206:         env:\n207:         - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n208:           valueFrom:\n209:             fieldRef:\n210:               fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n211:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n212:           value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n213:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n214:           valueFrom:\n215:             secretKeyRef:\n216:               name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n217:               key: password\n218:         - name: {{ .name }}\n219:           value: {{ .value }}\n220:         # ... extraEnv injected here\n221:         ports:\n222:         - name: http\n223:           containerPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n224:           protocol: TCP\n225:         livenessProbe:\n226:           httpGet:\n227:             path: /health\n228:             port: http\n229:           initialDelaySeconds: 10\n230:           periodSeconds: 10\n231:         readinessProbe:\n232:           httpGet:\n233:             path: /health\n234:             port: http\n235:           initialDelaySeconds: 5\n236:           periodSeconds: 5\n237:         resources: {{ toYaml .Values.workloadmanager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n238: ```\n239: \n240: #### Router Deployment\n241: \n242: ```yaml\n243: apiVersion: apps/v1\n244: kind: Deployment\n245: metadata:\n246:   name: agentcube-router\n247:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n248:   labels:\n249:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router\n250:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n251: spec:\n252:   replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicas }}\n253:   selector:\n254:     matchLabels:\n255:       app: agentcube-router\n256:   template:\n257:     metadata:\n258:       labels:\n259:         app: agentcube-router\n260:     spec:\n261:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n262:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n263:       {{- end }}\n264:       containers:\n265:       - name: agentcube-router\n266:         image: {{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\n267:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n268:         args:\n269:         - --port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n270:         - --debug\n271:         env:\n272:         - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n273:           valueFrom:\n274:             fieldRef:\n275:               fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n276:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n277:           value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n278:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n279:           valueFrom:\n280:             secretKeyRef:\n281:               name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n282:               key: password\n283:         - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n284:           value: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"\n285:         # ... extraEnv injected here\n286:         ports:\n287:         - name: http\n288:           containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n289:           protocol: TCP\n290:         livenessProbe:\n291:           httpGet:\n292:             path: /health/live\n293:             port: http\n294:           initialDelaySeconds: 1\n295:           periodSeconds: 2\n296:         readinessProbe:\n297:           httpGet:\n298:             path: /health/ready\n299:             port: http\n300:           initialDelaySeconds: 1\n301:           periodSeconds: 2\n302:         resources: {{ toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 10 }}\n303: ```\n304: \n305: #### WorkloadManager RBAC\n306: \n307: ```yaml\n308: # ServiceAccount\n309: apiVersion: v1\n310: kind: ServiceAccount\n311: metadata:\n312:   name: workloadmanager\n313:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n314: \n315: # ClusterRole\n316: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n317: kind: ClusterRole\n318: metadata:\n319:   name: workloadmanager\n320: rules:\n321: # Sandbox management\n322: - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n323:   resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n324:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n325: \n326: # Extension resources\n327: - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n328:   resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n329:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n330: \n331: # Warm pool status update\n332: - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n333:   resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n334:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n335: \n336: # CodeInterpreter management\n337: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n338:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n339:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n340: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n341:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n342:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n343: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n344:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n345:   verbs: [\"update\"]\n346: \n347: # AgentRuntime management\n348: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n349:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n350:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n351: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n352:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n353:   verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n354: \n355: # Pod read access\n356: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n357:   resources: [\"pods\"]\n358:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n359: \n360: # Token review for authentication\n361: - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n362:   resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n363:   verbs: [\"create\"]\n364: \n365: # Secret management\n366: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n367:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n368:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n369: \n370: # ClusterRoleBinding\n371: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n372: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n373: metadata:\n374:   name: workloadmanager\n375: roleRef:\n376:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n377:   kind: ClusterRole\n378:   name: workloadmanager\n379: subjects:\n380: - kind: ServiceAccount\n381:   name: workloadmanager\n382:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n383: ```\n384: \n385: #### Router RBAC (Optional)\n386: \n387: Rendered only when `router.rbac.create: true`:\n388: \n389: ```yaml\n390: # ServiceAccount\n391: apiVersion: v1\n392: kind: ServiceAccount\n393: metadata:\n394:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n395:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n396: \n397: # Role (namespace-scoped)\n398: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n399: kind: Role\n400: metadata:\n401:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n402:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n403: rules:\n404: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n405:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n406:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n407: \n408: # RoleBinding\n409: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n410: kind: RoleBinding\n411: metadata:\n412:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n413:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n414: roleRef:\n415:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n416:   kind: Role\n417:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n418: subjects:\n419: - kind: ServiceAccount\n420:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n421:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n422: ```\n423: \n424: #### Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n425: \n426: Rendered only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`:\n427: \n428: ```yaml\n429: # ServiceAccount\n430: apiVersion: v1\n431: kind: ServiceAccount\n432: metadata:\n433:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n434: \n435: # ConfigMap\n436: apiVersion: v1\n437: kind: ConfigMap\n438: metadata:\n439:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\n440: data:\n441:   agent-scheduler.conf: |\n442:     actions: \"allocate\"\n443:     tiers:\n444:     - plugins:\n445:       - name: predicates\n446:       - name: nodeorder\n447: \n448: # ClusterRole with comprehensive scheduling permissions\n449: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n450: kind: ClusterRole\n451: metadata:\n452:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n453: rules:\n454: # CRD management\n455: - apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]\n456:   resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]\n457:   verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n458: \n459: # Core resources\n460: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n461:   resources: [\"events\", \"pods\", \"pods/status\", \"pods/binding\"]\n462:   verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n463: # ... (additional pod-related permissions)\n464: \n465: # Deployment\n466: apiVersion: apps/v1\n467: kind: Deployment\n468: metadata:\n469:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n470: spec:\n471:   replicas: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas }}\n472:   template:\n473:     spec:\n474:       serviceAccountName: volcano-agent-scheduler\n475:       containers:\n476:       - name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n477:         image: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.tag }}\n478:         args:\n479:         - --scheduler-name=agent-scheduler\n480:         - --config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf\n481:         securityContext:\n482:           runAsNonRoot: true\n483:           runAsUser: 1000\n484:         volumeMounts:\n485:         - name: config\n486:           mountPath: /config\n487:         - name: empty\n488:           mountPath: /emptydir\n489:       volumes:\n490:       - name: config\n491:         configMap:\n492:           name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\n493:       - name: empty\n494:         emptyDir: {}\n495: ```\n496: \n497: ### CRD Definitions\n498: \n499: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n500: \n501: ```yaml\n502: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n503: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n504: metadata:\n505:   name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n506: spec:\n507:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n508:   names:\n509:     kind: AgentRuntime\n510:     plural: agentruntimes\n511:     shortNames: [ar]\n512:     singular: agentruntime\n513:   scope: Namespaced\n514:   versions:\n515:   - name: v1alpha1\n516:     served: true\n517:     storage: true\n518:     additionalPrinterColumns:\n519:     - name: NAME\n520:       type: string\n521:       jsonPath: .metadata.name\n522:     - name: PHASE\n523:       type: string\n524:       jsonPath: .status.phase\n525:     - name: SANDBOX\n526:       type: string\n527:       jsonPath: .status.sandboxRef.name\n528:     - name: AGE\n529:       type: date\n530:       jsonPath: .metadata.creationTimestamp\n531:     schema:\n532:       openAPIV3Schema:\n533:         type: object\n534:         properties:\n535:           spec:\n536:             required:\n537:             - maxSessionDuration\n538:             - podTemplate\n539:             - sessionTimeout\n540:             - targetPort\n541:             properties:\n542:               maxSessionDuration:\n543:                 type: string\n544:                 default: \"8h\"\n545:               sessionTimeout:\n546:                 type: string\n547:                 default: \"15m\"\n548:               targetPort:\n549:                 type: array\n550:                 items:\n551:                   type: object\n552:                   required: [port, protocol]\n553:                   properties:\n554:                     port:\n555:                       type: integer\n556:                     protocol:\n557:                       type: string\n558:                       enum: [HTTP, HTTPS]\n559:               podTemplate:\n560:                 type: object\n561:                 # Full PodSpec-like schema\n562: ```\n563: \n564: #### CodeInterpreter CRD\n565: \n566: ```yaml\n567: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n568: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n569: metadata:\n570:   name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n571: spec:\n572:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n573:   names:\n574:     kind: CodeInterpreter\n575:     plural: codeinterpreters\n576:     shortNames: [ci]\n577:     singular: codeinterpreter\n578:   scope: Namespaced\n579:   versions:\n580:   - name: v1alpha1\n581:     served: true\n582:     storage: true\n583:     subresources:\n584:       status: {}\n585:     schema:\n586:       openAPIV3Schema:\n587:         type: object\n588:         properties:\n589:           spec:\n590:             required: [template]\n591:             properties:\n592:               authMode:\n593:                 type: string\n594:                 enum: [picod, none]\n595:                 default: picod\n596:               maxSessionDuration:\n597:                 type: string\n598:                 default: \"8h\"\n599:               sessionTimeout:\n600:                 type: string\n601:                 default: \"15m\"\n602:               warmPoolSize:\n603:                 type: integer\n604:                 format: int32\n605:               template:\n606:                 type: object\n607:                 # Container template schema\n608: ```\n609: \n610: ## Error Handling\n611: \n612: ### Chart Validation Errors\n613: \n614: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n615: |-------|-----------|---------|\n616: | Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint failed: {detail}` |\n617: | Template render failure | 1 | `helm template failed: {detail}` |\n618: | CRD installation failure | 1 | `Failed to install CRD: {detail}` |\n619: | Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr is required in values` |\n620: | Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n621: \n622: ### Runtime Errors\n623: \n624: | Error | Component | Recovery |\n625: |-------|-----------|----------|\n626: | Redis connection refused | Router, WorkloadManager | Retry with exponential backoff |\n627: | Invalid Redis password | Router, WorkloadManager | Log error, fail health check |\n628: | RBAC permission denied | WorkloadManager | Log error, fail reconciliation |\n629: | CRD not found | All components | Fail startup, require manual CRD install |\n630: \n631: ## Testing Strategy\n632: \n633: ### Unit Tests\n634: \n635: **Location**: `manifests/charts/base/tests/` (to be created)\n636: \n637: ```yaml\n638: # tests/workloadmanager_test.yaml\n639: suite: WorkloadManager Deployment tests\n640: tests:\n641:   - it: creates Deployment with correct metadata\n642:     asserts:\n643:       - hasDocuments:\n644:           count: 1\n645:         documentIndex: 0\n646:         isKind:\n647:           of: Deployment\n648:       - equal:\n649:           path: metadata.name\n650:           value: workloadmanager\n651: \n652:   - it: sets replicas from values\n653:     set:\n654:       workloadmanager.replicas: 3\n655:     asserts:\n656:       - equal:\n657:           path: spec.replicas\n658:           value: 3\n659: \n660:   - it: injects correct environment variables\n661:     asserts:\n662:       - contains:\n663:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].env\n664:           content:\n665:             name: REDIS_ADDR\n666:             value: \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\"\n667: \n668:   - it: configures liveness probe correctly\n669:     asserts:\n670:       - equal:\n671:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.httpGet.path\n672:           value: /health\n673:       - equal:\n674:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.initialDelaySeconds\n675:           value: 10\n676: \n677:   - it: applies resource limits from values\n678:     set:\n679:       workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 1000m\n680:       workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 1Gi\n681:     asserts:\n682:       - equal:\n683:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.cpu\n684:           value: 1000m\n685: ```\n686: \n687: ### Integration Tests\n688: \n689: **Command**: `helm template test manifests/charts/base`\n690: \n691: Verify:\n692: 1. All templates render without errors\n693: 2. Generated YAML is valid\n694: 3. Conditional resources respect flags\n695: 4. Values overrides work correctly\n696: \n697: **Command**: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n698: \n699: Verify:\n700: 1. No linting errors or warnings\n701: 2. Chart structure is valid\n702: 3. All required files present\n703: \n704: ### E2E Tests\n705: \n706: **Scenario**: Full chart installation in Kind cluster\n707: \n708: ```bash\n709: # Create Kind cluster\n710: kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n711: \n712: # Install chart\n713: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n714:   --namespace agentcube \\\n715:   --create-namespace \\\n716:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n717:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n718:   --wait\n719: \n720: # Verify deployments are ready\n721: kubectl wait deployment/workloadmanager --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n722: kubectl wait deployment/agentcube-router --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n723: \n724: # Verify services are created\n725: kubectl get svc -n agentcube\n726: \n727: # Test with optional components\n728: helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n729:   --namespace agentcube \\\n730:   --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true \\\n731:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n732:   --wait\n733: \n734: # Verify optional components\n735: kubectl wait deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n736: kubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager\n737: kubectl get role/agentcube-router --namespace=agentcube\n738: \n739: # Cleanup\n740: kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n741: ```\n742: \n743: ## Dependencies\n744: \n745: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n746: |---------|---------|---------|\n747: | Helm | ≥3.0.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n748: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n749: | Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n750: | Volcano | Optional | Advanced scheduling (if enabled) |\n751: \n752: ## File Structure\n753: \n754: ```\n755: manifests/\n756: └── charts/\n757:     └── base/\n758:         ├── Chart.yaml                    # REQUIRED: Chart metadata\n759:         ├── values.yaml                   # REQUIRED: Default configuration\n760:         ├── .helmignore                   # REQUIRED: Packaging exclusions\n761:         ├── crds/\n762:         │   ├── agentruntime.yaml         # EXISTING: AgentRuntime CRD\n763:         │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml      # NEW: CodeInterpreter CRD\n764:         └── templates/\n765:             ├── _helpers.tpl              # Helper templates\n766:             ├── redis-secret.yaml         # Redis password Secret\n767:             ├── workloadmanager.yaml      # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n768:             ├── agentcube-router.yaml     # Router Deployment + Service\n769:             ├── rbac/\n770:             │   └── workloadmanager.yaml  # WorkloadManager RBAC\n771:             ├── rbac-router.yaml          # Optional Router RBAC\n772:             └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n773: ```\n774: \n775: ## Multi-Environment Support\n776: \n777: ### Development Environment\n778: \n779: ```yaml\n780: # values-dev.yaml\n781: router:\n782:   replicas: 1\n783:   resources:\n784:     limits:\n785:       cpu: 250m\n786:       memory: 256Mi\n787:     requests:\n788:       cpu: 50m\n789:       memory: 64Mi\n790: \n791: workloadmanager:\n792:   replicas: 1\n793:   resources:\n794:     limits:\n795:       cpu: 250m\n796:       memory: 256Mi\n797:     requests:\n798:       cpu: 50m\n799:       memory: 64Mi\n800: \n801: volcano:\n802:   scheduler:\n803:     enabled: false\n804: ```\n805: \n806: ### Production Environment\n807: \n808: ```yaml\n809: # values-prod.yaml\n810: router:\n811:   replicas: 3\n812:   resources:\n813:     limits:\n814:       cpu: 1000m\n815:       memory: 1Gi\n816:     requests:\n817:       cpu: 200m\n818:       memory: 256Mi\n819: \n820: workloadmanager:\n821:   replicas: 2\n822:   resources:\n823:     limits:\n824:       cpu: 1000m\n825:       memory: 1Gi\n826:     requests:\n827:       cpu: 200m\n828:       memory: 256Mi\n829: \n830: volcano:\n831:   scheduler:\n832:     enabled: true\n833:     replicas: 2\n834: ```\n835: \n836: ### Usage\n837: \n838: ```bash\n839: # Development\n840: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-dev.yaml \\\n841:   --set redis.addr=redis-dev:6379\n842: \n843: # Production\n844: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-prod.yaml \\\n845:   --set redis.addr=redis-prod:6379\n846: \n847: # Custom image registry\n848: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n849:   --set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/agentcube-router \\\n850:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=myregistry.com/workloadmanager\n851: ```\n852: \n853: ## Acceptance Checklist\n854: \n855: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n856: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n857: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n858: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n859: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n860: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n861: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n862: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n863: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n864: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n865: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n866: - [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n867: - [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n868: - [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n869: - [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n870: - [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n871: \n872: ## Open Questions\n873: \n874: 1. **External Redis Operator Integration**: Should the chart support automatic Redis provisioning via Redis Operator (e.g., Spotahome, OperatorHub)?\n875: \n876: 2. **Monitoring and Logging**: Should Prometheus scrape annotations, ServiceMonitor CRs, and Fluentd/ELK integration be included in the chart?\n877: \n878: 3. **Multi-Cluster Deployment**: Should the chart support deployment across multiple Kubernetes clusters with shared Redis backend?\n879: \n880: 4. **Default Values for Development**: Should the chart include a `values-dev.yaml` file with development-appropriate defaults out of the box?\n881: \n882: 5. **Ingress Configuration**: Should an Ingress resource be added for external access to Router and WorkloadManager services?\n883: \n884: 6. **Pod Disruption Budgets**: Should PDBs be configured for production deployments to ensure availability during node maintenance?\n\n(End of file - total 884 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n├── crds/\n│   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n│   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","time":{"start":1775879053374,"end":1775879053391}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879053397,"sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa3d0a8001EMUsejnCbmOCu6","messageID":"msg_d7aa3c639001nETap8AVBJkyib","sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_545b3a3a048a4ee0ad819c36","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** manifests  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L  \n6: **Stage:** ST-0 (pending)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Acceptance Criteria\n11: \n\n(End of file - total 11 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Tasks\n\n**Module:** manifests  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-0 (pending)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775879053369,"end":1775879053396}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879053400,"sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa3d6460016VlirJH3x1tsYQ","messageID":"msg_d7aa3c639001nETap8AVBJkyib","sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_eaa7483cb6d5420e99f4e675","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** sdk-python  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Package Structure & Utilities ✓\n11: \n12: - [x] **T1.1** Create `agentcube/__init__.py`\n13:   - Import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `code_interpreter`\n14:   - Import `AgentRuntimeClient` from `agent_runtime`\n15:   - Define `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n16:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n17:   - Verify: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` works\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.2** Create `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n20:   - Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)` base class\n21:   - Define `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` attributes\n22:   - Define `SessionError(AgentCubeError)` placeholder for future expansion\n23:   - Define `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)` placeholder for future expansion\n24:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n25:   - Verify: All exception classes instantiate correctly\n26: \n27: - [x] **T1.3** Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n28:   - Empty file (module marker)\n29:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n30:   - Verify: Module imports successfully\n31: \n32: - [x] **T1.4** Create `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n33:   - Import `requests`, `HTTPAdapter`, `Retry`\n34:   - Implement `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10, max_retries=0)`\n35:   - Configure retry strategy with `backoff_factor=0.1`, `status_forcelist=[429, 500, 502, 503, 504]`\n36:   - Mount `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`\n37:   - Return configured `requests.Session`\n38:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n39:   - Verify: Session has adapters mounted for http/https with correct pool sizes\n40: \n41: - [x] **T1.5** Create `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n42:   - Implement `read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str`\n43:   - Return file contents stripped\n44:   - Return `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`\n45:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n46:   - Verify: Returns empty string for missing file, stripped content for existing\n47: \n48: - [x] **T1.6** Create `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n49:   - Implement `get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO)`\n50:   - Create logger with stream handler\n51:   - Format: `%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s`\n52:   - Avoid duplicate handlers\n53:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py`\n54:   - Verify: Logger outputs formatted messages\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Phase 2: Control Plane Client ✓\n59: \n60: - [x] **T2.1** Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n61:   - Import all three client classes: `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n62:   - Define `__all__` with client names\n63:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n64:   - Verify: Clients importable from `agentcube.clients`\n65: \n66: - [x] **T2.2** Create `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n67:   - Import `ControlPlaneClient`, `os`, `requests`, utilities\n68:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n69:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n70: \n71: - [x] **T2.3** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__()`\n72:   - Parameters: `workload_manager_url`, `auth_token`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n73:   - Resolve `base_url` from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env\n74:   - Raise `ValueError` if URL missing\n75:   - Resolve auth token from arg or service account file\n76:   - Create session with `create_session()`\n77:   - Set headers: `Content-Type`, optional `Authorization`\n78:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n79:   - Verify: Instantiates with URL, uses env fallback, handles missing token gracefully\n80: \n81: - [x] **T2.4** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`\n82:   - Parameters: `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `metadata=None`, `ttl=3600`\n83:   - POST to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n84:   - JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata`\n85:   - Timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n86:   - Return `response.json()[\"sessionId\"]`\n87:   - Raise `ValueError` if `sessionId` missing\n88:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n89:   - Verify: Returns session ID from mock response\n90: \n91: - [x] **T2.5** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`\n92:   - Parameter: `session_id: str`\n93:   - DELETE to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n94:   - Return `True` on success or 404\n95:   - Return `False` on other errors (log warning)\n96:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n97:   - Verify: Idempotent on 404, logs on error\n98: \n99: - [x] **T2.6** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.close()`\n100:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n101:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n102:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## Phase 3: Data Plane Clients ✓\n107: \n108: - [x] **T3.1** Create `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n109:   - Import `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n110:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n111:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n112: \n113: - [x] **T3.2** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n114:   - Parameters: `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`, `base_url`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n115:   - Resolve `base_url`: use provided OR compute from `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name`\n116:   - Raise `ValueError` if can't resolve\n117:   - Create session, set `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n118:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n119:   - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, session header set\n120: \n121: - [x] **T3.3** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient._request()`\n122:   - Parameters: `method`, `endpoint`, `body=None`, `**kwargs`\n123:   - Build URL with `urljoin(self.base_url, endpoint)`\n124:   - Set `Content-Type: application/json` if body present\n125:   - Apply timeout from kwargs or defaults\n126:   - Return `requests.Response`\n127:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n128:   - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n129: \n130: - [x] **T3.4** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()`\n131:   - Parameters: `command: Union[str, List[str]]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n132:   - Convert string command to list\n133:   - Build JSON body: `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n134:   - Apply read timeout buffer: `timeout_value + 2.0`\n135:   - POST to `api/execute`\n136:   - Raise `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n137:   - Return `stdout` string\n138:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n139:   - Verify: Returns stdout, raises on non-zero exit\n140: \n141: - [x] **T3.5** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.run_code()`\n142:   - Parameters: `language: str`, `code: str`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n143:   - Support `python`, `py`, `python3`\n144:   - Write timestamped `.py` file via `write_file()`\n145:   - Execute via `python3 <file>` using `execute_command()`\n146:   - Raise `ValueError` for unsupported languages\n147:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n148:   - Verify: Python code executes correctly\n149: \n150: - [x] **T3.6** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.write_file()`\n151:   - Parameters: `content: str`, `remote_path: str`\n152:   - Base64 encode content\n153:   - POST JSON to `api/files`: `path`, `content`, `mode=\"0644\"`\n154:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n155:   - Verify: File created via base64 encoding\n156: \n157: - [x] **T3.7** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file()`\n158:   - Parameters: `local_path: str`, `remote_path: str`\n159:   - Read local file as binary\n160:   - POST multipart to `api/files` with `file`, `path`, `mode`\n161:   - Set `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly\n162:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n163:   - Verify: Multipart upload succeeds\n164: \n165: - [x] **T3.8** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.download_file()`\n166:   - Parameters: `remote_path: str`, `local_path: str`\n167:   - Clean path: `remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n168:   - GET from `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`\n169:   - Write chunks to local file\n170:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n171:   - Verify: File downloaded correctly\n172: \n173: - [x] **T3.9** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.list_files()`\n174:   - Parameter: `path: str = \".\"`\n175:   - GET from `api/files` with query `path`\n176:   - Return JSON response\n177:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n178:   - Verify: Returns file list\n179: \n180: - [x] **T3.10** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close()`\n181:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n182:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n183:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n184: \n185: - [x] **T3.11** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n186:   - Import `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n187:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n188:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n189: \n190: - [x] **T3.12** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n191:   - Parameters: `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n192:   - Compute `base_url` from `router_url` + namespace + agent_name path using `urljoin()`\n193:   - Create session with `create_session()`\n194:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n195:   - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, connection pool configured (10/10)\n196: \n197: - [x] **T3.13** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n198:   - GET from `self.base_url`\n199:   - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n200:   - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n201:   - Return session ID\n202:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n203:   - Verify: Extracts session ID from response header\n204: \n205: - [x] **T3.14** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()`\n206:   - Parameters: `session_id`, `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n207:   - Set headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n208:   - Apply timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or instance default\n209:   - POST JSON payload to `self.base_url`\n210:   - Return `requests.Response`\n211:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n212:   - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n213: \n214: - [x] **T3.15** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close()`\n215:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n216:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n217:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Phase 4: Configura