: \n76: - [ ] **T3.2** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()`\n77:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `router_url=None`, `verbose=False`, `session_id=None`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n78:   - Store instance attributes\n79:   - Initialize logger with verbose level\n80:   - Resolve `router_url` from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n81:   - Raise `ValueError` if router_url missing\n82:   - Bootstrap session_id if not provided via `_bootstrap_session_id()`\n83:   - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n84:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n85:   - Verify: Client instantiates, session bootstrapped or reused\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient._bootstrap_session_id()`\n88:   - Create temporary `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n89:   - Call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n90:   - Store result as `self.session_id`\n91:   - Close temporary client\n92:   - Return session ID\n93:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verify: Session ID bootstrapped from endpoint\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T3.4** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__enter__()` and `__exit__()`\n97:   - `__enter__`: return `self`\n98:   - `__exit__`: call `self.close()`\n99:   - Support context manager protocol\n100:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n101:   - Verify: `with` statement works\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T3.5** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()`\n104:   - Parameters: `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float] = None`\n105:   - Check `session_id` is set, raise `ValueError` if not\n106:   - Call `dp_client.invoke()` with session_id, payload, timeout\n107:   - Return `response.json()`\n108:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n109:   - Verify: Invocation returns parsed JSON\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T3.6** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.close()`\n112:   - Call `dp_client.close()`\n113:   - Log cleanup action\n114:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n115:   - Verify: Resources cleaned up\n11