{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879144672,"sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa41cbe001vLbJqC3nYUUeRU","messageID":"msg_d7aa40c5e001uibMMV7NjyjJR9","sessionID":"ses_2855c5349ffeGj7l251CZKkA6u","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_8d511d728095447cb92b9481","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md","content":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values Tasks\n\n**Module:** manifests  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-0 (pending)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Chart Metadata & Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create `Chart.yaml`\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`\n  - Set `name: agentcube`\n  - Set `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n  - Set `version: 0.1.0`\n  - Set `appVersion: \"1.0.0\"`\n  - Add keywords: `agent`, `sandbox`, `kubernetes`, `volcano`\n  - Add maintainers and home/sources metadata\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`\n  - Verify: `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes metadata validation\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create `values.yaml`\n  - Define global settings: `imagePullSecrets`, `nameOverride`, `fullnameOverride`\n  - Define `redis.addr` (required, empty default) and `redis.password` (optional)\n  - Define `router` configuration: replicas, image, service, resources, extraEnv, rbac\n  - Define `workloadmanager` configuration: replicas, image, service, resources, extraEnv\n  - Define `volcano.scheduler` configuration: enabled, replicas, image\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n  - Verify: All values accessible via `helm template`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Create `.helmignore`\n  - Ignore patterns: `*.md`, `*.log`, `*.tmp`, `.git/`, `tests/`, `*.swp`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore`\n  - Verify: Packaging excludes specified files\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Helper Templates\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create `_helpers.tpl`\n  - Define `agentcube.name` helper\n  - Define `agentcube.fullname` helper\n  - Define `agentcube.chart` helper\n  - Define `agentcube.labels` helper\n  - Define `agentcube.selectorLabels` helper\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl`\n  - Verify: Helpers render correctly in templates\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Redis Secret\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Create `redis-secret.yaml`\n  - Create Secret named `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis`\n  - Set key `password` with value from `.Values.redis.password`\n  - Use `b64enc` for base64 encoding\n  - Add standard labels\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml`\n  - Verify: Secret renders with correct password encoding\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: WorkloadManager Deployment\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Create WorkloadManager Deployment\n  - Set `apiVersion: apps/v1`, `kind: Deployment`\n  - Use `agentcube.fullname` helper for name\n  - Set replicas from `.Values.workloadmanager.replicas`\n  - Configure selector with `app: workloadmanager`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: Deployment metadata correct\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Configure WorkloadManager container\n  - Set image from `.Values.workloadmanager.image`\n  - Set `imagePullPolicy` from values\n  - Add args: `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=`\n  - Add env: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (downward API), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD` (from secret)\n  - Add ports: `http` with `containerPort` from values\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: Container spec correct\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Configure WorkloadManager probes\n  - Add `livenessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health`, port http, initialDelay=10, period=10\n  - Add `readinessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health`, port http, initialDelay=5, period=5\n  - Add resources from `.Values.workloadmanager.resources`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: Probes configured correctly\n\n- [ ] **T4.4** Create WorkloadManager Service\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: Service`\n  - Set type from `.Values.workloadmanager.service.type`\n  - Configure ports: port, targetPort from values\n  - Add selector `app: workloadmanager`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: Service routes to Deployment\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Router Deployment\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Create Router Deployment\n  - Set `apiVersion: apps/v1`, `kind: Deployment`\n  - Name: `agentcube-router`\n  - Set replicas from `.Values.router.replicas`\n  - Configure selector with `app: agentcube-router`\n  - Add conditional `serviceAccountName` if specified\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n  - Verify: Deployment metadata correct\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Configure Router container\n  - Set image from `.Values.router.image`\n  - Set `imagePullPolicy` from values\n  - Add args: `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`\n  - Add env: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`, `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n  - Construct `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` from release namespace and workloadmanager service port\n  - Add ports: `http` with `containerPort` from values\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n  - Verify: Container env vars correct\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Configure Router probes\n  - Add `livenessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health/live`, port http, initialDelay=1, period=2\n  - Add `readinessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health/ready`, port http, initialDelay=1, period=2\n  - Add resources from `.Values.router.resources`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n  - Verify: Probes configured correctly\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Create Router Service\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: Service`\n  - Set type from `.Values.router.service.type`\n  - Configure ports: port, targetPort from values\n  - Add selector `app: agentcube-router`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n  - Verify: Service routes to Deployment\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: WorkloadManager RBAC\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - Name: `workloadmanager`\n  - Add standard labels\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: ServiceAccount created\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n  - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRole`\n  - Add rules for:\n    - `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`: full CRUD\n    - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/*`: full CRUD + status updates\n    - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`: full CRUD + status + finalizers\n    - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes`: get/list/watch + status updates\n    - `pods`: get/list/watch\n    - `tokenreviews`: create\n    - `secrets`: full CRUD\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: ClusterRole permissions complete\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n  - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n  - Reference ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n  - Reference ServiceAccount `workloadmanager` in release namespace\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: Binding connects SA to ClusterRole\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Router RBAC (Optional)\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Create Router RBAC templates (conditional)\n  - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n  - Create ServiceAccount named `agentcube-router` (or from values)\n  - Create Role (namespace-scoped) for secrets management\n  - Create RoleBinding connecting SA to Role\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verify: RBAC only renders when enabled\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Create Volcano ServiceAccount\n  - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n  - Verify: ServiceAccount renders when enabled\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Create Volcano ConfigMap\n  - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n  - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap`\n  - Data: `agent-scheduler.conf` with actions and tiers config\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n  - Verify: ConfigMap contains scheduler config\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Create Volcano ClusterRole\n  - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n  - Comprehensive permissions for scheduling:\n    - CRDs: create/get/list/watch/delete\n    - Pods: full lifecycle management\n    - Events: create/get/list/watch\n    - Nodes: get/list/watch\n    - Namespaces: get/list/watch\n    - Services/ConfigMaps: get/list/watch\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n  - Verify: ClusterRole has scheduling permissions\n\n- [ ] **T8.4** Create Volcano ClusterRoleBinding\n  - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n  - Reference ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - Reference ServiceAccount `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n  - Verify: Binding connects SA to ClusterRole\n\n- [ ] **T8.5** Create Volcano Deployment\n  - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n  - Set replicas from `.Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas`\n  - Configure container with image from values\n  - Add args: `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, `--config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf`\n  - Mount ConfigMap at `/config`\n  - Add securityContext: `runAsNonRoot: true`, `runAsUser: 1000`\n  - Add emptyDir volume\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n  - Verify: Deployment configures scheduler correctly\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: CRDs\n\n- [ ] **T9.1** Verify `agentruntime.yaml` CRD completeness\n  - Check group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - Check names: kind, plural, shortNames, singular\n  - Check scope: Namespaced\n  - Check version: v1alpha1 with printer columns\n  - Verify schema: spec requirements (maxSessionDuration, podTemplate, sessionTimeout, targetPort)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n  - Verify: CRD is valid and complete\n\n- [ ] **T9.2** Create `codeinterpreter.yaml` CRD\n  - Set group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - Set names: kind `CodeInterpreter`, plural `codeinterpreters`, shortNames `ci`\n  - Set scope: Namespaced\n  - Set version: v1alpha1 with printer columns (NAME, PHASE, SANDBOX, AGE)\n  - Add subresources: `status: {}`\n  - Define schema with:\n    - `authMode`: enum [picod, none], default picod\n    - `maxSessionDuration`: string, default \"8h\"\n    - `sessionTimeout`: string, default \"15m\"\n    - `warmPoolSize`: integer (optional)\n    - `template`: container template object\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n  - Verify: `kubectl apply -f` succeeds\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: Chart Validation\n\n- [ ] **T10.1** Run `helm lint`\n  - Command: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n  - Fix all errors and warnings\n  - Verify: No lint errors\n\n- [ ] **T10.2** Run `helm template`\n  - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis.default.svc:6379\"`\n  - Verify: All templates render without errors\n  - Verify: Generated YAML is valid\n\n- [ ] **T10.3** Test conditional rendering (Volcano disabled)\n  - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=false`\n  - Verify: No Volcano resources in output\n  - Verify: WorkloadManager and Router present\n\n- [ ] **T10.4** Test conditional rendering (Volcano enabled)\n  - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n  - Verify: Volcano ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, Deployment present\n  - Verify: Volcano ClusterRole and ClusterRoleBinding present\n\n- [ ] **T10.5** Test conditional rendering (Router RBAC enabled)\n  - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true`\n  - Verify: Router ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding present\n\n- [ ] **T10.6** Test values overrides\n  - Test replica overrides: `--set router.replicas=3 --set workloadmanager.replicas=2`\n  - Test resource overrides: `--set router.resources.limits.cpu=1000m`\n  - Test image overrides: `--set router.image.repository=myregistry/router`\n  - Verify: Overrides apply correctly in rendered templates\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11: E2E Testing (Optional/Kind Cluster)\n\n- [ ] **T11.1** Create Kind cluster\n  - Command: `kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e`\n  - Verify: Cluster is running\n\n- [ ] **T11.2** Install chart\n  - Command: `helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\"`\n  - Verify: Installation succeeds\n\n- [ ] **T11.3** Verify Deployments\n  - Wait for WorkloadManager: `kubectl wait deployment/workloadmanager --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m`\n  - Wait for Router: `kubectl wait deployment/agentcube-router --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m`\n  - Verify: Both deployments available\n\n- [ ] **T11.4** Verify Services\n  - Command: `kubectl get svc -n agentcube`\n  - Verify: workloadmanager and agentcube-router services exist\n\n- [ ] **T11.5** Verify RBAC\n  - Command: `kubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager`\n  - Command: `kubectl get clusterrolebinding/workloadmanager`\n  - Verify: RBAC resources exist\n\n- [ ] **T11.6** Test upgrade with optional components\n  - Command: `helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true --set router.rbac.create=true`\n  - Verify: Upgrade succeeds\n  - Verify: Volcano deployment created\n  - Verify: Router RBAC created\n\n- [ ] **T11.7** Cleanup\n  - Command: `kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e`\n  - Verify: Cluster deleted\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ Chart structure complete: `Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `.helmignore`\n2. ✅ All templates render without errors (`helm template`)\n3. ✅ `helm lint` passes with no errors or warnings\n4. ✅ Redis secret created with correct password encoding\n5. ✅ WorkloadManager Deployment has correct env vars, probes, resources\n6. ✅ Router Deployment has `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` constructed correctly\n7. ✅ WorkloadManager RBAC: ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n8. ✅ Router RBAC: conditional, namespace-scoped Role + RoleBinding\n9. ✅ Volcano Scheduler: conditional, full scheduling stack\n10. ✅ CRDs: AgentRuntime (existing) and CodeInterpreter (new) valid\n11. ✅ Conditional rendering works for optional components\n12. ✅ Values overrides work for multi-environment support\n13. ✅ `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n14. ✅ All deployments become available\n15. ✅ RBAC permissions correctly scoped\n16. ✅ Service ports and selectors correctly configured\n17. ✅ Helper templates work consistently across all manifests\n18. ✅ Labels follow Kubernetes conventions (`app.kubernetes.io/*`)\n19. ✅ Security contexts configured (Volcano runs as non-root)\n20. ✅ Health check endpoints match component implementations\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-0: Implementation pending\n- Redis password: stored in Secret, referenced via `secretKeyRef`\n- WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: constructed dynamically from release namespace\n- Router RBAC: disabled by default, enable via `router.rbac.create: true`\n- Volcano Scheduler: disabled by default, enable via `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n- CRDs: installed in `crds/` directory (Helm 3 convention, installed before templates)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775879144651,"end":1775879144669}}}}
